    notes:
      "## Clinical Context — Dual Agonism as the Modern Incretin Frontier\n\nTirzepatide is the molecule that established dual-incretin receptor agonism as a viable pharmaceutical class for both type 2 diabetes and obesity. The SURPASS trial program (T2D) and SURMOUNT trial program (obesity) generated the clinical evidence base. SURMOUNT-5 (2024-2025) was the first head-to-head trial of tirzepatide vs semaglutide for weight management — tirzepatide produced ~20% mean body weight reduction vs ~14% for semaglutide at 72 weeks, establishing superiority in weight outcome.\n\nThe SURMOUNT-OSA 2024 results led to the expanded FDA indication for obstructive sleep apnea in adults with obesity — the first pharmacotherapy approval for OSA based on weight-loss-mediated mechanism.\n\n## Two Pharmaceutical Formulations\n\n### Mounjaro (SubQ, T2D)\n- Pre-filled multi-dose pen and KwikPen formats\n- Doses: 2.5, 5, 7.5, 10, 12.5, 15mg weekly\n- Titration: 2.5mg start (4 weeks) → 5mg standard maintenance, escalate as needed\n- T2D indication; commonly used off-label for weight management\n\n### Zepbound (SubQ, obesity / OSA)\n- Pre-filled multi-dose pen format\n- Same dose range as Mounjaro\n- 16-20 week titration to maintenance\n- Indicated for adults with BMI ≥30, or ≥27 with weight-related comorbidity; also approved for OSA in adults with obesity (2024 expanded indication)\n\n## Tirzepatide vs Semaglutide — The Practical Comparison\n\n**Weight loss magnitude:** tirzepatide > semaglutide (SURMOUNT-5: ~20% vs ~14% at 72 weeks). The ~6-percentage-point difference at maximum doses is clinically meaningful.\n\n**Glycemic control in T2D:** tirzepatide > semaglutide (SURPASS-2: greater HbA1c reduction; greater proportion achieving HbA1c <7%).\n\n**Tolerability per weight lost:** clinical observation suggests tirzepatide produces slightly less GI symptom burden per kilogram lost; direct comparative tolerability data is limited.\n\n**Body composition profile:** body composition substudies suggest tirzepatide may produce slightly more favorable adipose-vs-lean-mass loss ratio, though lean mass loss still occurs without resistance training and adequate protein.\n\n**Cardiovascular evidence:** semaglutide has SUSTAIN-6 (T2D) and SELECT (obesity without diabetes) CVOT data; tirzepatide SURPASS-CVOT is ongoing — semaglutide currently holds the more robust CV outcome evidence base.\n\n**Renal evidence:** semaglutide has FLOW 2024; tirzepatide does not yet have a comparable renal outcome trial.\n\n**Pharmaceutical formulation breadth:** semaglutide has SubQ + oral routes; tirzepatide is SubQ-only.\n\n**Practical clinical decision:** for users prioritizing weight loss magnitude — tirzepatide. For users with established CV disease prioritizing CV outcome evidence — semaglutide currently has the deeper evidence base. For users requiring oral route — semaglutide (Rybelsus). For users with OSA — tirzepatide has the specific indication.\n\n## Titration — Tolerability Reality\n\nGI side effect profile parallels semaglutide. The 16-20 week tirzepatide titration mitigates tolerability concerns. Strategies for tolerability mitigation are identical to semaglutide considerations (slow titration, lower meal volumes, low fat, hydration, anti-nausea adjuncts, pause at lowest tolerated effective dose).\n\nMany users achieve adequate weight loss response at 5mg, 7.5mg, or 10mg without need to advance to 15mg maximum — advancing further produces additional weight loss but with substantially diminishing returns and increased side effect burden.\n\n## Lean Mass Preservation — Same Adjunct Considerations as Semaglutide\n\nSubstantial portion of tirzepatide-induced weight loss is lean tissue without resistance training and adequate protein. Body composition substudies suggest possibly more favorable adipose-vs-lean ratio than semaglutide but lean mass loss still occurs.\n\nMitigation requires deliberate intervention identical to semaglutide context:\n- Protein 1.6-2.2g/kg target body weight\n- Resistance training 2-4x/week\n- Adequate creatine\n- Some clinical contexts add GH-axis support (CJC-1295, ipamorelin, tesamorelin)\n\n## Cardiovascular and Other Outcome Trial Status\n\n**SURPASS-CVOT:** ongoing cardiovascular outcome trial in T2D; results expected. Preliminary data from SURPASS program is supportive of CV safety and likely benefit.\n\n**SURMOUNT-OSA (2024):** established OSA outcome benefits in obesity; basis for expanded Zepbound indication.\n\n**SURMOUNT-MMO (ongoing):** morbidity and mortality outcomes in obesity.\n\n**Renal outcome trial:** not yet a dedicated trial comparable to semaglutide's FLOW.\n\n## Anesthesia / Surgical Considerations\n\nIdentical to semaglutide considerations. Hold weekly tirzepatide 1 week before elective surgery per ASA 2023 guidance. Disclose use to anesthesia team. Aspiration precautions for emergency surgery regardless of cessation timing.\n\n## Hormonal Contraceptive Interaction\n\nUnique tirzepatide consideration not shared by semaglutide labeling: gastric emptying delay may reduce oral contraceptive absorption and effectiveness. Pharmaceutical labeling recommends non-oral contraceptive method for 4 weeks after starting tirzepatide and 4 weeks after each dose escalation. Relevant for users of childbearing potential.\n\n## Synergies\nIdentical to semaglutide. **GH-axis peptides** for lean mass preservation. **BPC-157** for GI healing. **Comprehensive nutrition** with elevated protein and adequate fiber. **Resistance training**.\n\n## Clinical Trial Citations Worth Knowing\nSURPASS program (T2D efficacy — SURPASS-2 vs semaglutide head-to-head). SURMOUNT program (obesity efficacy — SURMOUNT-1 foundational, SURMOUNT-5 head-to-head vs semaglutide, SURMOUNT-OSA 2024).\n\n## Evidence Quality\nMost recent generation of incretin pharmaceutical with rapidly accumulating evidence base. FDA approvals across T2D, obesity, and OSA. Greatest weight loss magnitude in head-to-head data with semaglutide. Long-term safety profile less mature than semaglutide due to shorter time on market but comparable safety signals to date.\n\n## Research vs Anecdote\nResearch: SURMOUNT-5 head-to-head establishes tirzepatide superiority for weight loss vs semaglutide; SURMOUNT-OSA establishes new mechanism-of-action class for OSA pharmacotherapy; rapidly accumulating evidence base. Anecdote: substantial wellness-clinic and obesity-medicine prescribing; community familiarity with titration patterns; subjectively reported lower GI burden per weight lost than semaglutide. Decision frame: foundational dual-incretin RA for T2D, obesity, and OSA; superior weight loss magnitude vs semaglutide; tolerability mitigation strategies identical to semaglutide; coordinate anesthesia and OCP considerations specifically; mandatory protein and resistance training for lean mass preservation.",
    tags: ["tirzepatide", "Mounjaro", "Zepbound", "GIP/GLP-1 dual agonist", "T2D", "obesity", "OSA", "weight loss", "FDA-approved", "SURPASS", "SURMOUNT", "MTC boxed warning"],
